history.content:
How would this be for spring? I understand that it's not the easiest but I think I need to take more classes next semester to make up for my lighter current semester.

I was taking 170, 61C and 16A this semester but had to drop 61C since working was cutting into my time and I just wasn't keeping up. I'll have more time next semester to fully dedicate to classes, however 61C will be with Weaver which I hear will be much worse than with Garcia.

My other question is about 168 vs 188 with these classes. I think that these two are relatively lighter upper divs but which one would be less of a time commitment to still get a good grade in? or is this just way too hard and I shouldn't take a upper div
history.subject: Spring 2020: 61C + 16B + 168/188?
